node.text: wwWawww

Spending time with family, cycling around the city, a train ride to Busan and just a nice bowl of curry. These are some of the things healthcare workers in Singapore are looking forward to after Covid-19 is over. 
The journey may be long, but always keep the end goal in mind.
Thank you for your contribution 🌹🌹🌹🌹
Looking forward to dine out
I will pray for the safety of all of you. Thank you so much for fighting and saving lives on the front line! ❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️
Looking forward to no clusters after these few days.  No visits please.. Its against the law.
My father 😂
I look forward to having a lot of sex with a lot of women and having children I do not know about.
Hi! Please checkout my studygram for free notes! Thank you 🦋 stay safe!
@shaifulsaleh awwww so sweet leh hahahah
I look forward to school and more homework so that I can be busy. I feel sad because I was not as busy during CB.
It may took a longer time for up to one year for the Covid 19 pandemic to ends. But I hope that everything goes well as per normal after the Covid 19 ends.
Salute all health hero's 💚💜❤🙏
Treat better to mother nature n make a better world to all of us❤️
Endless suppy. Bubble tea
I just want go downstairs play volleyball that's all I look forward to
thank you for your service, let us essential workers fight off covid 19 together ❤️
This would not have been so bad if more action was taken earlier and the fw dorm situation could have been prevented... Waiting for the IB to respond hehe
Train to Busan? Really?
Keep up the good work. Stay safe.
Train to busan, zombies😂
wwWawww
